# Agentic harness (always on)

This repo runs a portable agent harness under `.claude/`. The full cross-tool
manual is [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md); the project router is
[CLAUDE.md](../../CLAUDE.md). Read both for anything project-specific.

## Always

- **Invoke the most specific skill(s) BEFORE writing code.** Skills under
  `.claude/skills/` carry project conventions your training data lacks. Match the
  most specific; invoke 2–3 per task. See
  [`.claude/rules-topical/skill-dispatch.md`](../../.claude/rules-topical/skill-dispatch.md).
- **Senior-agent discipline.** Non-trivial work is iterative: gather context →
  act through a tool → verify → stop only when the goal is genuinely met. Answer
  before acting. No hacks. Verify before "done".
- **Confirm before big/irreversible work** (multi-file change, migration,
  push/PR, shared-contract change): restate intent + a short plan first.
- **Always-on constraints** live in [`.claude/rules/`](../../.claude/rules/);
  on-demand deep dives in [`.claude/rules-topical/`](../../.claude/rules-topical/).
